1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,600
Good morning 早晨各位

2
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:06,900
I was trying to remember when's the last time I was here preaching

3
00:00:06,900 --> 00:00:08,400
It's been a while

4
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:11,800
我想一下我上一次來這裡講道的時候是幾時呢?

5
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:13,800
可能已經是一段時間了

6
00:00:13,800 --> 00:00:15,800
It's all exciting for me to be here

7
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:19,200
For those of you who don't know my parents grew up in Hong Kong

8
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:22,400
我很興奮可以來到這裡當中

9
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,600
有些如果對我不是很認識的

10
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:27,200
我的父母都是在香港長大

11
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,000
So I'm Cantonese

12
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,000
所以我是廣東人

13
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,800
And I feel like I'm at home when I'm here with you all

14
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:37,400
我覺得在家的樣子非常之舒服

15
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:41,000
If you could show the first slide with some pictures

16
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,200
The next slide

17
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,800
I just want to update you

18
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,200
Since I haven't been here for a while

19
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,200
And some of you might not know

20
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:50,000
My family

21
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:50,800
Next picture

22
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:52,000
You can see the Christmas picture

23
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,800
We just took this last month

24
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:59,800
我是給大家一個想將我最近的情況

25
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:01,200
跟大家分享一下

26
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:04,200
這個是在聖誕節的時候我們拍的照

27
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:07,400
So many of you know my wife Sherry and my son Asher

28
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:10,400
Asher is now 13 years old and in 7th grade

29
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:12,200
我的太太是Shirley

30
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:14,400
我兒子是Asher

31
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:21,000
他現在已經是七年級13歲

32
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,000
And also many of you might know we are a foster family

33
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,200
And right now we welcomed an 18-year-old foster son

34
00:01:28,200 --> 00:01:29,000
Into our family

35
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:31,600
So he doesn't always come on Sundays

36
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:33,000
But you might see him around

37
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,200
我們都是有領養了一個18歲的年輕人

38
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,200
他不是經常來到這個教會

39
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,200
有時你都見到他

40
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,400
And also in July 2024

41
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:46,600
My mom passed away after 5 years of illness

42
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:50,600
我媽媽是在2024年就離開世

43
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:55,600
她是有5年的時間都是有病的

44
00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:58,200
And I've noticed since I haven't had as much chance to practice

45
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:02,000
That my Cantonese is kind of not as good anymore

46
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:05,600
你知道我沒那麼多機會去練習的時候

47
00:02:05,600 --> 00:02:08,600
所以我的廣東話不是講得那麼好

48
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:11,600
So hopefully you forgive me if I want to spend more time with you

49
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:14,000
So I can practice my tones

50
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:20,600
我希望可以用多點時間和大家一起練習我的廣東話

51
00:02:20,600 --> 00:02:23,800
But today we are going to be talking about the leadership of our church

52
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:25,400
Who we call elders

53
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,600
我們今天會是講我們教會的領導

54
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,400
我們所講的長老

55
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:32,000
The Bible says that an elder is someone in the church

56
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:34,600
Who helps lead and take care of God's people

57
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:37,200
聖經上說長老就是在教會裏面

58
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:40,800
幫助帶領和照顧神的子民的人

59
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,400
Jesus is the head of the church

60
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,600
And the elders are like loving coaches

61
00:02:45,600 --> 00:02:47,400
基督就是教會的頭

62
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:51,400
而長老就好像是一個有愛心的教練

63
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:53,400
Coaches who watch over the church family

64
00:02:53,400 --> 00:02:54,600
And teach God's word

65
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,600
And show others what it looks like to follow Jesus

66
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:59,600
這個教練就是守望著教會裏面的人

67
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:02,600
教導神的話語和以他的生命

68
00:03:02,600 --> 00:03:05,600
去示範怎樣去跟隨耶穌

69
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:07,600
I've been blessed to serve as an elder of this church

70
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,000
For the last 10 years

71
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:13,600
過去10年我很有福氣能夠在這個教會裏面擔任長老

72
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:15,400
Now we know that these next few years

73
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:18,000
will be a season of change for our church family

74
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,400
我們知道未來幾年

75
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:22,600
這個教會會進入一個很轉變的季節

76
00:03:22,600 --> 00:03:25,000
Elder Tyke just retired from his role as elder

77
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:26,200
at the end of last year

78
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:29,800
Tyke 長老在上年底的時候就正式的退休了

79
00:03:29,800 --> 00:03:32,000
That leaves us across all our congregations

80
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,400
with just 3 elders

81
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:37,800
我們這三個語言的堂會那裏

82
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:40,800
只剩下3個長老

83
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:43,600
And the reality is with over 500 members

84
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:45,000
or people here at T4C

85
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,800
there are not enough elders to lead

86
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,800
and to care for everyone

87
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:51,800
事實上T4C有差不多500人聚會

88
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:55,600
而長老的人是不足夠帶領和照顧這麼多人的

89
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:58,000
And it's not just elders either

90
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,400
並不是單單是長老

91
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,800
You all, we all have been praying

92
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,800
for a Cantonese pastor for a long time now

93
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:11,200
我們都為我們粵語部要有一個牧師討告

94
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,000
But our current staff

95
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:14,600
including Pastor Fred, Pastor Mike

96
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:16,200
and our children's director Jody

97
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:18,200
are all close to retirement age

98
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:20,800
但是Fred 牧師和Mike 牧師

99
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:23,000
兒童士工的主任 Jody

100
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:25,200
他們已經接近退休的年齡了

101
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,200
And we are also talking about church planting

102
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:30,600
我們都有討論過席堂

103
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:33,600
So we are going to need even more elders and pastors

104
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:36,600
所以我們更需要更多的長老和更多的牧者

105
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:38,000
So what does this mean?

106
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,600
這一切是提醒我們什麼呢?

107
00:04:41,600 --> 00:04:44,000
We need leaders to step up now

108
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:46,800
我們要多些領袖去站出來

109
00:04:46,800 --> 00:04:50,000
Because we are going to need more mature leaders in the coming years

110
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,600
所以在我們未來幾年

111
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:54,400
我們要更多的成熟的領袖

112
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:55,800
And God's vision for the church

113
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:59,200
always requires a new generation of leaders to step up

114
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,400
神對教會的心意

115
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:04,200
一向都是要新一代願意來裝備來服侍

116
00:05:04,200 --> 00:05:05,800
So as we look at God's word this morning

117
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:07,400
I want to talk about the weight

118
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:11,200
the glorious weight and responsibility of church leadership

119
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:14,200
所以當我們今天一起打開神的話語的時候

120
00:05:14,200 --> 00:05:17,000
我想講一下教會的領導

121
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,800
怎麼是榮耀的重責

122
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:20,800
And I want to be clear

123
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:23,000
It's not just for official elders

124
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:27,800
but for anyone God's calling to step up into leadership

125
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:31,800
不單止是正式的這個長老是任何神可以呼召的

126
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:33,200
都要能夠參與

127
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:35,400
And you might not feel like you're ready for it right now

128
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:39,400
but God is preparing you for your part in the future

129
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:41,600
你可能覺得自己未必準備好

130
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:44,200
但是神已經準備了你

131
00:05:44,200 --> 00:05:48,800
將來要你成就你要盡的那個本分

132
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:50,200
Let's start with a word of prayer

133
00:05:50,200 --> 00:05:52,600
我們開始我們的禱告

134
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:55,600
Our great God we worship you this morning

135
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:58,800
偉大的神我們在這裡來敬拜你

136
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:01,400
We worship you with our presence

137
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:04,200
我們用我們的來臨來敬拜你

138
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:05,400
Our attention

139
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,800
我們的專心

140
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:08,400
And our response to your word

141
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:11,200
我們對你的話語的回應來敬拜你

142
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:13,800
We pray that you would give us your wisdom and your peace

143
00:06:13,800 --> 00:06:18,000
我們祈求你給我們智慧和平安

144
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:20,200
It's in Jesus' wonderful name that we pray

145
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,400
和主耶穌奇妙的名來禱告

146
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:24,800
Amen

147
00:06:24,800 --> 00:06:28,000
OK, let's start by digging into our Bible verses

148
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,000
好,我們開始的時候

149
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:31,400
我們看看聖經裡面的經文

150
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:34,200
So starting with 1 Peter 5

151
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:36,600
彼得前書第五章

152
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:40,200
OK, there's a section here, let's see

153
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,600
Be shepherds of God's flock

154
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,800
that is under your care watching over them

155
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,400
not because you must

156
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:46,800
but because you are willing

157
00:06:46,800 --> 00:06:48,000
as God wants you to be

158
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:50,000
not pursuing dishonest gain

159
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,000
but eager to serve

160
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,400
not lording it over those entrusted to you

161
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,600
but being examples to the flock

162
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,800
我作了長老的

163
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:59,600
作基督受苦的見證

164
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:02,800
同享後來所要顯現的榮耀的

165
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:05,200
勸你們在中間和我作長老的人

166
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:08,600
務要牧養你中間神的群羊

167
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:10,800
按著神旨意照顧他們

168
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,200
不是出於勉強

169
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,800
乃是出於甘心

170
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,200
也不是因為貪財

171
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,800
乃是出於樂意

172
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,800
也不要合際所託付你們的

173
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:21,000
乃是作群羊的榜樣

174
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,800
到你要牧長顯現的時候

175
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,000
你們必得

176
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:26,600
永不需嘗那榮耀的冠冕

177
00:07:26,600 --> 00:07:28,200
Peter is telling the church elders

178
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:30,200
to shepherd the flock

179
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:33,600
彼得是吩咐教會的長老

180
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,800
要牧養這個羊群

181
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,000
This is a metaphor from everyday life

182
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,600
back in ancient world

183
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:45,000
這個比喻來自古代日常生活

184
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,800
Today most of us aren't farmers or shepherds

185
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:50,000
今日我們大部分人都不是農夫

186
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:51,800
都不是牧羊人

187
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:52,800
But in Peter's time

188
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:54,000
shepherds were everywhere

189
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,800
and everyone knew what they did

190
00:07:55,800 --> 00:07:58,200
但是在彼得那個時代的時候

191
00:07:58,200 --> 00:08:00,000
牧羊人是隨時都可以見到的

192
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:00,800
每個人都知道

193
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,600
牧羊人在做的是什麼

194
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:03,800
This is a picture actually

195
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,800
from when I was in the Middle East

196
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:08,800
這幅相就是當我在中東的時候

197
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:09,600
我拍的

198
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,800
And I learned that like

199
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,000
there are sheep everywhere

200
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:14,400
我學到的就是

201
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:16,000
在中東那個地方的時候

202
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:17,600
這些羊周圍都見到的

203
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,600
When you are driving around

204
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,000
there are sheep in the streets

205
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,000
當你在開車的時候

206
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,800
你看到這些羊在街上

207
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,600
So what is it like to be a shepherd?

208
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:33,200
作為一個牧羊人的時候會是怎樣的呢?

209
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:36,200
Okay, so guiding and feeding

210
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:39,200
第一就是引導和餵養

211
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,800
Shepherds spend all day

212
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:42,600
taking care of their sheep

213
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:43,600
牧羊人每天

214
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,800
經常都是這樣照顧牠們的羊群

215
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:48,000
They are making sure the sheep have food

216
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:49,200
and water and shelter

217
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:52,200
他們確保這個羊有食物

218
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:54,000
有水和有地方

219
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,000
They help to heal them

220
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:56,400
when they are injured or sick

221
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,000
當這個羊受傷的時候

222
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,000
或者生病的時候

223
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,800
他們會幫忙去醫治牠們

224
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,800
Without a shepherd

225
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:03,600
the sheep easily wander off

226
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:05,400
get lost or fall into danger

227
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:07,000
如果沒有這個羊的帶領的時候

228
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,400
這個羊很容易迷失

229
00:09:10,400 --> 00:09:12,600
走失了或者跌下危險

230
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,800
Shepherds also protect their sheep

231
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:21,000
牧羊人同時保護這些羊群

232
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,600
They protect them from predators

233
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,000
and they guide them to safe pastures

234
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,600
牧羊人保護這些羊群

235
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:29,400
不會受到野獸的攻擊

236
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,800
帶牠們去安全的草場

237
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:33,000
They watch for trouble

238
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,800
and they stand between the sheep and harm

239
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,800
牧羊人留意四周圍的危險

240
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:41,200
保養這些羊群免受傷害

241
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:44,200
Shepherds also lead their sheep

242
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:46,800
牧人也是帶領這些羊群

243
00:09:46,800 --> 00:09:48,800
The sheep learn the shepherd's voice

244
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:51,200
and they follow them when they are called

245
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:54,400
羊會認到牧羊人的聲音

246
00:09:54,400 --> 00:09:56,000
當牧羊人被叫的時候

247
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:57,600
牧羊人會跟著牧羊人

248
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,800
True shepherds lead by caring relationship

249
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:02,200
not by force or by yelling

250
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:05,600
真正的牧人會用關係和關心去帶領

251
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,000
不是說要強迫他們

252
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:09,800
或者大聲地喝他們

253
00:10:09,800 --> 00:10:12,000
You know, often in today's world

254
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,800
leadership is about being in charge

255
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,600
or being above others

256
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:18,000
你知道在現在的世界裡面

257
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,400
領導往往就是掌權

258
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:23,000
或者是在人的高高在上

259
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:26,200
But real leadership is about gaining trust

260
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:28,400
through love and daily presence

261
00:10:28,400 --> 00:10:29,800
但是在整個國裡面

262
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:32,800
真正的領導就是保護人們

263
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,200
關心和服侍人

264
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:36,000
It means getting close to people

265
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:38,400
protecting, caring, serving

266
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:40,000
and guiding by example

267
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,200
真的是走近他們

268
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,400
保護他們

269
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,400
服侍他們

270
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:47,000
用自己的生命作為一個榜樣去帶領

271
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:50,200
And that's what Jesus as the good shepherd does for us

272
00:10:50,200 --> 00:10:51,400
這就是耶穌

273
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:54,200
我們這個好牧人為我們所做的

274
00:10:54,200 --> 00:10:57,600
That's what elders are called to be examples of

275
00:10:57,600 --> 00:10:59,000
長老就是被呼召出來

276
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:01,600
活出這個榜樣

277
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:04,400
Shepherding is spending time with people

278
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:07,800
牧羊就是要用時間跟人一起相處

279
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:10,200
Really getting to know the church family

280
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:14,400
真正認識這個教會裡面的家人

281
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:17,400
Shepherding is walking alongside someone

282
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:18,800
through their struggles

283
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:21,400
是陪伴一個人走過他的困難

284
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:23,000
Or helping to share wisdom

285
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:24,800
for small and big decisions

286
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:26,400
或者是有大小的決定的時候

287
00:11:26,400 --> 00:11:28,600
分享跟他分享的智慧

288
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:31,200
Shepherding is leading by showing

289
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:33,400
牧羊就是以身作則

290
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,600
Not just telling

291
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,600
不是就這樣用口講

292
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:39,000
It's building trust that helps the whole church

293
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,400
grow closer to Jesus

294
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,600
是建立這個信任

295
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:47,800
幫助這個教會更加親近耶穌

296
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,200
Right now a lot of people

297
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:51,600
are going through difficult times

298
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:54,200
現在時候可能會有很多人

299
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:57,200
是經歷到這個困難

300
00:11:57,200 --> 00:11:59,400
They need shepherds to help guide them

301
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:04,200
他們需要這個牧羊人去引導他們

302
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:07,000
The next passage we'll look is from James

303
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:10,800
第二個經文我們要看的就是由雅各書

304
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:12,800
James 3.1 warns

305
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,800
Not many of you should become teachers

306
00:12:14,800 --> 00:12:15,800
my fellow believers

307
00:12:15,800 --> 00:12:17,000
because you know that

308
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:19,800
we who teach will be judged more strictly

309
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,200
他說三章第一節說

310
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:24,200
我們的弟兄們不要作多人的師父

311
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:28,600
因為曉得我們要受更重的判斷

312
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:30,000
Now teaching in the church

313
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,600
isn't just about preaching a sermon

314
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,200
or leading a Bible class

315
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:36,000
在教會裡面教導不是單單說道

316
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,000
或者是帶茶經班

317
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,600
It's really anytime we help someone understand

318
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:42,400
what it means to follow Jesus

319
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:45,200
是每一次當我們幫助別人

320
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,600
去明白怎麼樣跟隨耶穌的時候

321
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,000
這就是教導

322
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:52,000
Now this might happen in conversations

323
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,200
in your community

324
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:56,000
or small groups or everyday life

325
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,200
這可能是跟人聊天的時候

326
00:12:58,200 --> 00:12:59,200
在小組裡面

327
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,600
跟人一起走的時候

328
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:04,400
或者在日常的生活裡面

329
00:13:04,400 --> 00:13:06,800
Also teaching is not about status

330
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:10,000
or seeking attention

331
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,400
還有教導不是關於地位

332
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:17,400
或者是要被人去注意

333
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,000
It's about influence

334
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:22,800
and with influence comes real responsibility

335
00:13:22,800 --> 00:13:25,800
教導是關於影響力

336
00:13:25,800 --> 00:13:29,200
而有影響力的就有真正的責任

337
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,200
Elders and teachers

338
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:32,200
don't just pass on information

339
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:34,200
they help open up the Bible and say

340
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:36,400
this is what it means to follow Jesus

341
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:40,200
同時長老不是只是傳遞一個訊息

342
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:42,400
就是打開聖經的時候

343
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,400
然後跟人說

344
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:47,800
這樣就是跟隨耶穌

345
00:13:47,800 --> 00:13:49,400
So the warning in James is that

346
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:50,600
if we get it wrong

347
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:53,000
we could mislead or wound

348
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:55,000
or confuse God's people

349
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:59,800
所以在雅各這樣警告我們的時候

350
00:13:59,800 --> 00:14:02,400
就是說如果我們教錯了人的時候

351
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:04,600
就可能會誤導或者傷害

352
00:14:04,600 --> 00:14:07,400
或者令神所愛的人得到困擾

353
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,200
And unfortunately

354
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,800
we see so many examples of this in the world today

355
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,600
在我們現在的世界的時候

356
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:15,400
我們就會看到很多這樣的例子

357
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,800
So called leaders and teachers

358
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,800
who are misleading people

359
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:25,200
有很多的教師不是真正是教錯人的

360
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:27,000
But if we get it right

361
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,000
但如果我們真的教到正確的時候

362
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,000
If we are truly teaching God's word

363
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:34,400
如果我們真的按神的話語去教人的時候

364
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,000
We can help people build up their faith

365
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,600
我們就能夠幫助他們建立信心

366
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:40,600
And encourage lifelong discipleship

367
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:42,800
又鼓勵他們一生作主的門徒

368
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,800
This warning in James

369
00:14:43,800 --> 00:14:46,400
isn't meant to make us afraid of teaching

370
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:51,600
這個警告不是說要我們很害怕去教人

371
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:54,000
We shouldn't be afraid of helping others to grow

372
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:57,800
我們不應該害怕幫助別人在屬靈的成長

373
00:14:57,800 --> 00:14:59,400
It just reminds us that God

374
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:02,200
takes what we say and what we do seriously

375
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,400
它只不過是提醒我們

376
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:05,800
神很認真地看我們

377
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:07,200
我們所講所做的

378
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,800
神會很認真地看

379
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:11,400
Because what we teach can affect people

380
00:15:11,400 --> 00:15:12,800
in very real ways

381
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:13,800
因為我們所講

382
00:15:13,800 --> 00:15:16,000
我們所教導的

383
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:19,000
會影響人的生命

384
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,600
The third passage is from James 5:14

385
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:24,600
第三個經文就是由《雅各書》第五章第十四節

386
00:15:24,600 --> 00:15:29,400
James links eldership closely with pastoral care

387
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:33,400
雅各將長老的職份和牧羊的關係

388
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,000
緊緊地連在一起

389
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:35,800
Let me read it again

390
00:15:35,800 --> 00:15:37,800
Is anyone among you sick?

391
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:40,400
Let them call the elders of the church to pray over them

392
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:43,200
and anoint them with oil in the name of the Lord

393
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,600
這次的經文是這麼說

394
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,800
你們中間有病了的

395
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:51,400
他就該請教會的長老來

396
00:15:51,400 --> 00:15:52,800
他們可以奉主的名

397
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,600
用油抹他 為他禱告

398
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:58,000
So the word that's used for anoint here

399
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:01,000
means to rub or to pour oil on someone

400
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:02,800
在這裡「羔抹」這個字

401
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:06,400
就是用油去塗在人的身上

402
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:07,400
In biblical times

403
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,600
that's what people did for healing

404
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:10,600
在聖經的時代

405
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:12,000
這些人就是上堅的

406
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,800
用一個治療的方法

407
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:16,200
It was their medicine

408
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:18,600
這些就是他們的藥物

409
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:20,800
So James is telling the church

410
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,800
to gather to elders to pray

411
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:24,600
but also to care for the sick

412
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,000
with practical help

413
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,600
所以雅各祭的意思就是

414
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:30,600
要教會的長老為這些病人來禱告

415
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:33,400
同一個時候

416
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:36,000
就用實際的方法來照顧他們

417
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:37,800
就好像用藥物一樣

418
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,600
Sometimes we think that elders

419
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:42,000
are just meeting planners or sermon givers

420
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,800
有時我們以為長老就是

421
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:46,200
只不過是開會

422
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:47,600
在這裡安排一些事

423
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:49,000
或者是講一下道

424
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:52,600
But God calls elders to step into those crisis moments

425
00:16:52,600 --> 00:16:55,600
但是神呼召長老在危機的時候

426
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,800
隨時效命

427
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:59,000
Maybe it's sitting by the hospital beds

428
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:02,000
可能在病床那裡坐在旁邊

429
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:03,400
Praying with the suffering

430
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:06,000
或者是和受苦的人一起來禱告

431
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,600
Caring for both spiritual and physical needs

432
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:13,800
或者是屬於身體上要照顧的軟弱的人

433
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:14,600
In those moments

434
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:17,400
the elder's job is not to be above others

435
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,200
在這個時候長老的角色

436
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:21,200
不是說要高高在上

437
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,600
But to come alongside

438
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:24,200
就是並肩而行

439
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:25,800
Not just to teach

440
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:27,400
不是說要去教導

441
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:30,800
But to come alongside in the hardships of life

442
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:34,200
是親身走入生命裡面的困難

443
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,800
So this extends the role of elders

444
00:17:35,800 --> 00:17:37,200
beyond just preaching

445
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:39,400
所以這個是延伸到

446
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:45,200
長老的職責不是說超過教導

447
00:17:45,200 --> 00:17:47,000
You might say that elders are spiritual

448
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:48,400
first responders

449
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,800
你可以說長老是

450
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:52,400
屬靈的第一線的回應者

451
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,600
And their ministry includes

452
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,800
both the spiritual and the physical

453
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:58,000
他們的角色是

454
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,800
包括了身體上和屬靈上

455
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:03,200
To model both compassion and faith

456
00:18:03,200 --> 00:18:04,400
in all circumstances

457
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:07,800
無論在哪一個處境裡面

458
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:10,400
都活出這個憐憫和信心

459
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:11,800
In this way elders show

460
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:14,000
the church's care for its members

461
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:17,000
在這個方式裡面

462
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,600
長老就成為教會對信徒的關愛

463
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:21,200
這個具體的表現

464
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:23,600
To connect the needs of the body

465
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,800
to the grace and the healing of Jesus

466
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:28,000
將教會肢體裡面的需要

467
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:32,600
連結在基督的恩典和意志裡面

468
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:34,000
So that's what our three passages

469
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,600
are talking about today

470
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:40,800
這個就是我們三節的經文所說的

471
00:18:40,800 --> 00:18:42,200
Let's talk a little bit more about

472
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:44,200
what elders are

473
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:49,800
我們說一下長老是什麼

474
00:18:49,800 --> 00:18:52,000
The word that's translated as elders

475
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:54,800
in these verses is presbyterus

476
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:58,400
在聖經裡面翻譯長老這個字

477
00:18:58,400 --> 00:19:01,200
就是presbyterius這個字

478
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:04,600
The word literally means elder or older one

479
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:07,200
or someone known for wisdom and maturity

480
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:09,200
聖經裡面的原意就是

481
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,600
這個字的原意就是年長者

482
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:13,800
或者是較成熟的人

483
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:19,000
或者是以智慧和成熟見稱的人

484
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:20,600
This message I hate to admit it

485
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:24,800
I am now an older person

486
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,200
我不是很想去承認

487
00:19:26,200 --> 00:19:29,400
但是我已經是年紀都長了

488
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,600
But we can see from the Bible

489
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,600
from the earliest days of Israel

490
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:36,200
the God's people appointed groups of older people

491
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:39,000
older men to lead and to guide

492
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:42,200
我們看到就是早期的

493
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:43,800
以色列早期的開始的時候

494
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,800
神就是已經是揀選一群

495
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:48,800
年紀大的有智慧的人去帶領

496
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:52,600
There were elders who served in the Sanhedrin in Jerusalem

497
00:19:52,600 --> 00:19:55,800
在耶路撒冷的公會裡面

498
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:58,400
有長老在這裡服侍

499
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:01,000
There were elders who served in the local synagogues

500
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:03,600
有不同在或者是

501
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:06,200
在地方的教會裡面

502
00:20:06,200 --> 00:20:08,000
都有長老在這裡服侍

503
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:09,800
And this idea of eldership

504
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:12,000
was adopted by the first Christians

505
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,600
我們知道早期教會的時候

506
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:18,400
都很快地承接了這個長老的制度

507
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:21,200
The church in Jerusalem gathered elders

508
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:24,000
耶路撒冷的教會是聚集這個長老

509
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:27,600
And Paul and Barnabas made sure to

510
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:29,000
that every church they started

511
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,600
had its own group of elders

512
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,400
而保羅和巴拿巴都確保

513
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:34,800
在每一個建立這個地方教會的時候

514
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:37,000
都有一組的長老

515
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,800
So when scripture addresses elders

516
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:41,400
it's not just referring to a formal office

517
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:45,600
所以當聖經提到長老的時候

518
00:20:45,600 --> 00:20:48,200
不是單單只是一個正式的職位

519
00:20:48,200 --> 00:20:52,400
It's also inviting the older, mature and wise people

520
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:55,000
to step up in faith

521
00:20:55,000 --> 00:21:00,400
都是邀請這些年紀比較大

522
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:05,000
信心成熟和有智慧的人站出來

523
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:06,800
These people are to share their guidance

524
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,800
their experience and their spiritual insight

525
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:10,000
with the church family

526
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:13,000
這些人站出來就是在教會裡面

527
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,000
分享他們的經驗

528
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:17,200
他們的屬靈的洞見

529
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:19,800
So any of you who are further along

530
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,400
in your faith journey

531
00:21:21,400 --> 00:21:26,400
所以你們每一個在信心的路上

532
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,600
已經是走得很前了

533
00:21:28,600 --> 00:21:33,200
Those who might be called older

534
00:21:33,200 --> 00:21:36,000
年紀是比較大一點的

535
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:39,400
We need you to use your age and your wisdom

536
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:41,400
for the good of the church family

537
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,800
我們是要你的年紀

538
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:48,800
你的智慧來祝福整個教會

539
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:51,800
But even for those who are young

540
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:54,600
但是除了之外

541
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:58,200
就算是年紀比較輕的

542
00:21:58,200 --> 00:22:00,000
The responsibilities that we just talked about

543
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:02,800
in the verses of teaching, shepherding and ministry

544
00:22:02,800 --> 00:22:06,000
are to be part of our daily lives

545
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,200
我們剛才所講的

546
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:10,200
我們的教導、牧養、服侍

547
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,600
都是我們生活的每一個部分

548
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:16,800
For every maturing Christian, not just elders

549
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:20,800
是給所有成熟的信徒

550
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:24,000
不只是單單是長老

551
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,400
We see in the New Testament

552
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:28,200
that believers are encouraged over and over again

553
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:30,000
to love one another

554
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:33,000
我們在新約裏面我們看到

555
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,400
一再二再而三這樣去

556
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:38,400
鼓勵我們彼此去相愛

557
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:40,800
To encourage one another with the truth

558
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:43,400
是用這個真理去鼓勵大家

559
00:22:43,400 --> 00:22:45,400
To care for each other's needs

560
00:22:45,400 --> 00:22:47,000
彼此照顧

561
00:22:47,000 --> 00:22:48,400
To serve one another

562
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:51,600
彼此去服侍

563
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:53,200
So we want all believers

564
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,400
to do those things that we just talked about

565
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:57,000
所以我們想所有的信徒

566
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:00,200
都做這些以上我所講的東西

567
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:02,400
So eldership really is

568
00:23:02,400 --> 00:23:06,600
part of the maturing process of every Christian

569
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,800
所以這個長老都是

570
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:13,800
我們每一個信徒成熟的過程裏面

571
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:14,800
都出現的

572
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,400
And as we look for elders

573
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:19,000
we're not just saying "you" or "you"

574
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:23,200
當我們去選長老的時候

575
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:24,200
我們不是就這樣說

576
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:25,400
是你是你

577
00:23:25,400 --> 00:23:27,400
We're looking for those who are already

578
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:29,200
exhibiting these characteristics

579
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:32,800
我們是去選一些

580
00:23:32,800 --> 00:23:36,800
已經展示出這些特質的人

581
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:39,000
So I think in God's plan for the church

582
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,400
each one of us should be growing

583
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:43,600
in all of these abilities

584
00:23:43,600 --> 00:23:45,600
我覺得我們每一個人

585
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:48,200
都應該在這方面

586
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:50,000
在這些本能方面

587
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,800
繼續在這裏成長

588
00:23:51,800 --> 00:23:53,200
To shepherd others

589
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:54,800
去牧養別人

590
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:55,800
To teach others

591
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:56,800
去教導別人

592
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:58,000
To minister to others

593
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:00,200
去服侍別人

594
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:01,600
OK

595
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:05,200
There was a lot of me talking just now

596
00:24:05,200 --> 00:24:07,800
剛才你聽過我講了很多樣東西

597
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:10,200
I want you to take some time to think about

598
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,800
how it applies to your life

599
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:12,800
我想你們想一下

600
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:14,600
怎樣將我所講的東西

601
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:16,400
是應用在你的生命裏面呢

602
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:19,000
So why don't we just take 30 seconds or so

603
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:20,800
and think about this question

604
00:24:20,800 --> 00:24:25,400
我們想你用30秒的時間去想一下以下這個問題

605
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:28,000
If we are all called as Christians

606
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:31,000
to grow in teaching shepherding ministry

607
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:35,000
What is God calling you to work on right now?

608
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:41,400
如果神呼召我們要做這方面的事

609
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:44,000
教導牧養去服侍的時候

610
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:48,000
神現在是呼召你要做哪一方面呢?

611
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:52,000
And practically what steps can you take this week to practice?

612
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,000
還有具體方面

613
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:59,000
這個星期你可以採取什麼行動去操練和實踐以上的東西?

614
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:02,000
I want you to think about it right now for about 30 seconds

615
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:06,000
我想你用大約30秒的時間去想一下這一方面

616
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:22,000
Okay, I hope you have some ideas

617
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:25,000
我希望你們已經是有些意念

618
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:29,000
Cause we need each of you to do your part so that we can grow

619
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:33,000
我希望我們每一個都要盡我們自己的本份

620
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,000
讓我們教會能夠成長

621
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:39,000
We already talked about how there is not enough elders to do all the work

622
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:43,000
我們已經講過我們不夠長老去做所有的工作

623
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:47,000
We can only function as a family if everyone does their part

624
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:54,000
我們在教會裡的家庭要每個人做自己的本份

625
00:25:54,000 --> 00:26:00,000
So we just talked about how everyone has a role to teach and to shepherd and to minister

626
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:05,000
我們每一個人都有一個角色去教導、去牧養和去服侍

627
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:08,000
So does that mean that I don't need to do anything as an elder?

628
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:13,000
那是不是代表我做一個長老我不需要做什麼呢?

629
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:20,000
I think what sets apart the elders is the breadth of the responsibility of their calling

630
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:27,000
我相信長老與眾不同就是長老的責任是廣闊的

631
00:26:27,000 --> 00:26:31,000
Even though all of us are called to teach and to shepherd and to minister

632
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:35,000
the elders do the same things for the whole church

633
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:42,000
雖然每一個人都有一個角色去教導、牧養和去服侍

634
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:46,000
但是長老是為整個教會來服侍的

635
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:52,000
The elders' teaching must faithfully guide the congregations in truth

636
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:59,000
長老的教導都是要在真理裡面引導整個教會

637
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:04,000
The elders' shepherding extends to all kinds of needs for all members

638
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:08,000
他們的牧養是伸延到所有弟兄姊妹各種不同的需要

639
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:14,000
And the elders' ministry calls them to model and coordinate care for the entire body

640
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:22,000
他們的侍奉是要以自己的生命作為榜樣和協調幫助教會關顧的工作

641
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:26,000
So remember the Bible tells us that Jesus is the head of the church

642
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:29,000
聖經告訴我們基督就是教會的頭

643
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:33,000
He's the one that leads and directs and gives life to the whole body

644
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:40,000
耶穌就是帶領、指引和給生命給整個教會的群體

645
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:50,000
每一個人的領袖包括長老都可以取代這個位置

646
00:27:54,000 --> 00:28:03,000
那麼長老是如何進入這個位置呢?

647
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:07,000
我們想想我們的身體

648
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:13,000
我們知道我們的頭就是給所有的指令

649
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:27,000
但我們知道我們的神經系統包括脊椎

650
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:31,000
是連結和協調我們身體每一個部份

651
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:39,000
或者作為一個例子

652
00:28:39,000 --> 00:28:44,000
長老就好像一個脊椎

653
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:53,000
他們是作為一個連結和協調的工作

654
00:28:53,000 --> 00:29:02,000
是幫助我們的頭和我們其他身體的部份連結在一起

655
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:12,000
所以最主要的工作不是關於權力、侍奉

656
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:18,000
而是裝備身體其他部份

657
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:25,000
是幫助每一位信徒發現他們神給他們的恩賜

658
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:27,000
在信心裏面成長

659
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:31,000
是學習如何彼此服侍

660
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:40,000
我們的教會的主題在耶福所書就是這樣

661
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:55,000
長老和牧師的角色就是裝備各位信徒

662
00:29:55,000 --> 00:30:02,000
當長老有這樣的方式服侍的時候

663
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:06,000
教會就成為一個很合一的身體

664
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:14,000
每一部份都得到支持都可以裝備

665
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:21,000
所以長老不是出於權力而是出於一個牧人的心去引領

666
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:40,000
我們會有一連串的講道

667
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:44,000
是關於長老積分榮耀的重責

668
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:49,000
這個重責是什麼意思呢?

669
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:57,000
並不是說所有我們的工作、我們所有的會議

670
00:30:57,000 --> 00:31:08,000
是我們要向神交代和有影響力

671
00:31:15,000 --> 00:31:23,000
我們對人的靈魂、他們的信仰、他們的生命有非常大的影響力

672
00:31:23,000 --> 00:31:38,000
是,神也說他們將來要在神面前交仗

673
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:51,000
這是一個非常令人驚慌但也帶有榮耀的

674
00:31:51,000 --> 00:32:05,000
神竟然用我一個這麼不完善的人去服侍他,真是一個很大的榮耀

675
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:21,000
我們都很想看到將來在永恆當中你怎樣去尊崇我們的神

676
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:33,000
所以我們被呼召去做一個長老是非常之榮耀的

677
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:42,000
我們怎樣將這些應用在我們每一個人的生命裡面呢?

678
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:48,000
第一個應用是給每一位的

679
00:32:48,000 --> 00:33:03,000
雖然神不是呼召我們做長老,但祂也想我們都有長老的特質

680
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:13,000
我們引導、裝備、教導、服侍、牧養

681
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:22,000
我們每一個人都要去培養這些特質

682
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:37,000
當我們這樣做的時候,整個教會是會興旺的

683
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:47,000
我們第二個應用是不要等,我們開始去帶領

684
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:54,000
我們當中有很多人已經有神給這些恩賜

685
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:07,000
我們可以用這些恩賜在正常的環境裡面或平時

686
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:25,000
我們有很多的侍奉,例如在兒童的侍工裡面,主日學裡面,崇拜裡面,都要很多人的侍奉

687
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:36,000
或者你可以請一些人來到你家裡一起吃東西

688
00:34:36,000 --> 00:34:44,000
如果你看見有人受傷,你可以在他旁邊安慰他

689
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:54,000
或者你可以發一些郵件給他,鼓勵他,幫助他

690
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:03,000
第三個應用就是我們可以踏上長老的呼召

691
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:12,000
當中有神正在呼召你踏上長老的角色

692
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:19,000
不要讓猶豫或者害怕來阻止你

693
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:28,000
做一個長老並不是代表我有所有的答案

694
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:34,000
並不是要做一個十全十美的信徒

695
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:41,000
是有一個願意去服事,願意去聆聽的心

696
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:52,000
如果你有這個感受,你可以跟長老或牧師說一下

697
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:58,000
你知道,我們的教會正在等待一個廣東話的牧師

698
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:07,000
我想再次提醒大家,聖經中的模式就是領袖可以從教會裡面被認出

699
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:25,000
如果我們當中有一個人走出來,去受裝備成為我們語言部的牧師的時候,真是一個很大的祝福

700
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:38,000
如果你想走這條路的時候,我們知道整個教會會幫助你

701
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:53,000
會支持你和裝備你

702
00:36:53,000 --> 00:37:05,000
我也為這件事而禱告,希望神會呼召你願意踏出這個信心的一步

703
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:12,000
或者我可以比較精準一點

704
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:23,000
或者你會說我是一個很年輕的信徒或初信,我可以做些什麼呢?

705
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:31,000
我們可以學習,可以看看神給你的恩賜是什麼

706
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:40,000
或者你可以想一下你怎樣去服事我們整個的教會

707
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:48,000
可能會為人煮一餐飯,或者打電話給人

708
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:56,000
